Description: Shell of a gastropod mollusc of the 'Pectunailus zonalis' species.
Curator's comments: Found in box of unregistered shells with other shells that had handwritten slips written by Petrie identifying the shell species and naming Naukratis as the provenance. These notes were presumably written in 1884-1885 when Petrie excavated at Naukratis, although they could have been written in 1885-1886, when he visited the site. Although not definitely from Naukratis, this is the most likely provenance. Same shell as 2012,5015.1,which has a note by Petrie: ''Pectunailus zonalis Medit. Nebireh Naucratis'
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (WC.36)
